-- Tencent Plans to Invest $1 Billion in E-Commerce Unit
-- B y   J i m   J i a
-- 2012-05-24T19:12:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/tencent-plans-to-invest-1-billion-in-e-commerce-unit.html
Tencent Holdings Ltd. (700) , China’s
biggest Internet company, said it plans to invest $1 billion in
its independently run e-commerce unit to build a “new-
generation” business-to-consumer platform.  The company also appointed President Lau Chi Ping as the
chairman of Tencent E-Commerce Holding Co., according to a
 statement  posted on its website yesterday, citing Chief
Executive Officer Ma Huateng.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jim Jia in New York at 
